cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a method for skull stripping in MRI scans using a combination of Active Shape Model (ASM) and Convolutional Neural Network (CNN). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of prior knowledge and post-processing methods such as Conditional Random Field and Gaussian Process indicates that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of neural networks further suggests that the paper may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which may also make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
